# Constant Fold Comparison Functions

## Description

Evaluates comparison expressions (=, <>, <, >, BETWEEN, IN) and
boolean operations (AND, OR, NOT) at compile time when all operands
are constants. Chains with boolean simplification to eliminate
always-true or always-false predicates.

**When to apply**: Comparison where both sides are constants, or
boolean expressions that can be resolved.

**Why it works**: `10 > 5` is always TRUE. Folding to TRUE enables
predicate elimination upstream.

## Implementation

```rust
rw!("fold-eq"; "(= ?a ?b)" => { FoldCmp("?a", "?b", Eq) } if both_const("?a", "?b")),
rw!("fold-neq"; "(<> ?a ?b)" => { FoldCmp("?a", "?b", Neq) } if both_const("?a", "?b")),
rw!("fold-lt"; "(< ?a ?b)" => { FoldCmp("?a", "?b", Lt) } if both_const("?a", "?b")),
rw!("fold-gt"; "(> ?a ?b)" => { FoldCmp("?a", "?b", Gt) } if both_const("?a", "?b")),
rw!("fold-lte"; "(<= ?a ?b)" => { FoldCmp("?a", "?b", Lte) } if both_const("?a", "?b")),
rw!("fold-gte"; "(>= ?a ?b)" => { FoldCmp("?a", "?b", Gte) } if both_const("?a", "?b")),
rw!("fold-between";
    "(between ?a ?lo ?hi)" => { FoldBetween("?a", "?lo", "?hi") }
    if all_const("?a", "?lo", "?hi")
),
```

## Test Cases

```sql
-- Before
SELECT * FROM t WHERE 10 > 5 AND 'abc' = 'abc';
-- After
SELECT * FROM t WHERE TRUE AND TRUE;
-- Then: SELECT * FROM t;  (after boolean simplification)
```

```sql
-- Negative: column reference
SELECT * FROM t WHERE x > 5;
-- Cannot fold: x is a column
```

